From c2e73d0db8f084c02e99c7f424a25e868fe3edb1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: netborg <137700136+netborg-afps@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Wed, 3 Dec 2025 17:31:49 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 44/61] [dxvk] Switch to implicit VRR frame pacing

vkWaitForPresentKHR() times are not reliable to determine V-Blank times, as they depend on tight guarantees of the compositor and the graphics driver. The previous VRR mode regularly went into V-Sync buffering and its usage on Wayland was limited. Although we couldn't measure the V-Sync buffering to this fine degree, this became pretty clear during play-testing.

This implicit VRR pacing derives V-Blanks based on render-finished times and completely ignores any results from vkWaitForPresentKHR(). This also greatly improves compatibility and it now can be used on Xwayland and native Wayland.
